Sub/Import version 0.5
======================

Ever wanted to require() a file just for it's subroutines but had to end up
copying and pasting because the file executed code? If the answer to the
previous question was /^yes!?/i then this is the module for you! It will
cleanly extract subroutines from a given file and import them into the
current package.

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install

DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

	Carp
	IO::File
	Data::Dumper
	Regexp::Common
	Text::Balanced

